{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17636597","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17636597"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:30:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:30:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17592"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17592","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17592"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.11,0.64,0.04,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10306"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71444"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10306","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10306"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17592"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56953"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4911"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"9993"},{"type":"tags","id":"9995"},{"type":"tags","id":"10010"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24098"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24116"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24117"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71444","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71444"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe gastrocolic reflex is an important physiological mechanism that coordinates different parts of the digestive system.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the gastrocolic reflex?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Increased gastric acid secretion in response to colonic distension","Decreased colonic motility in response to gastric emptying","Increased colonic motility in response to gastric distension","Increased colonic absorption in response to gastric emptying","Decreased gastric motility in response to colonic distension"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eincreased colonic motility in response to gastric distension\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct description of the gastrocolic reflex. When food enters and distends the stomach, signals are sent via the parasympathetic nervous system to increase colonic motility. This coordinated response helps to move contents through the colon and often results in the urge to defecate after meals.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased gastric motility in response to colonic distension\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the opposite direction of the actual reflex\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased gastric acid secretion in response to colonic distension\u003C/strong\u003E - While gastric acid secretion is regulated by various mechanisms, it is not controlled by colonic distension\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased colonic motility in response to gastric emptying\u003C/strong\u003E - The reflex increases rather than decreases colonic motility\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased colonic absorption in response to gastric emptying\u003C/strong\u003E - The reflex affects motility rather than absorption\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis reflex is particularly active after breakfast, when it combines with the normal increase in colonic motility that occurs upon waking. It represents an important mechanism for maintaining digestive efficiency by creating space for incoming food.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The gastrocolic reflex is a physiological response where eating stimulates colonic motility via the parasympathetic nervous system.","This reflex helps maintain digestive efficiency by creating space for incoming food through promoting defecation.","The gastrocolic reflex is strongest after breakfast due to the combined effects of waking and eating."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019","Malone JC, Thavamani A. Physiology, Gastrocolic Reflex [Internet]. PubMed. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2021. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK549888/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56953"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17592"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56953","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56953"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-18T16:23:42+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-18T16:24:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10306"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71444"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/ap